Requirements:

- Django 1.1 or higher (http://www.djangoproject.com/)
- PostgresSQL version 8.3 or higher (http://www.postgresql.org/)
- Psycopg (http://initd.org/psycopg/)
- feedparser.py (http://www.feedparser.org/)
- django-cron

To get the web application running locally using the Django development web server:

- Create a database to be used for this website with PostgresSQL.
- Update settings_dev with your proper settings.
- Sync the DB with the project's initial schema and data, by running the following command within the project root: python manage.py syncdb
- Start the website with the following command from the project root: sudo python manage.py runserver --settings=settings 127.0.0.1:80
- Visit http://127.0.0.1/, the homepage should load.
